thread.title: President of Ireland coming to visit
thread.title_full: President of Ireland coming to visit | The Seattle Times

author: Daniel Beekman
title: President of Ireland coming to visit
text:
The president of Ireland, Michael Higgins, will visit Seattle later this week, a spokesman for Mayor Ed Murray said Monday.
Higgins will take part in several events, said spokesman Viet Shelton.
“I do believe there will be some interaction (with Murray),” Shelton said.
Further details about the trip will be forthcoming, he said.

The Irish Times reported Monday that Higgins and his wife, Sabina Higgins, are leaving home Tuesday for an eight-day visit to Seattle, San Francisco, Sacramento and Berkeley, Calif.
Ireland’s United States embassy shared the Irish Times report via Twitter on Monday.
Higgins will deliver two keynote speeches during the trip, including one at the University of Washington on the role of technology in sustainable development, the report said.
He’ll meet with Murray on Wednesday and on Thursday will visit Sammamish’s Skyline High School, where students play Gaelic football, the report said.
Higgins will visit Microsoft’s Redmond campus and will meet with people from the Seattle area’s Irish community, according to the report.
Ireland’s government is a parlimentary democracy in which the president has a mainly ceremonial role.
Murray traveled to Ireland last September, visiting Galway, a Seattle sister city, and meeting with Irish Prime Minister Enda Kenny in Dublin. Kenny had traveled to Seattle in 2013 to highlight a purchase of Boeing jets by Ryanair, an Irish airline.
China’s President, Xi Jinping, toured the Seattle area last month.
